 IMPACT OF VIDEODISC TECHNOLOGY ON JOINT MARKETS' IMPLICATIONS FORPUBLISHERS AND PRINTERS.     DESCRIBES THE TECHNOLOGY AND EQUIPMENT BEING DEVELOPED FOR VIDEO AND OPTICALDISCS BY A NUMBER OF COMPANIES AND THEIR MARKETING STRATEGY. THE ALTERNATIVESTO VIDEO DISC, E.G. VIDEO TAPE, VIEWDATA, PERSONAL COMPUTERS AND CABLE ANDSATELLITE TELEVISION, ARE CONSIDERED AND THE MAIN ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGESOF EACH ARE ASSESSED. THE APPLICATIONS, POTENTIAL AND CHARACTERISTICS OF VIDEOAND OPTICAL DISCS ARE DISCUSSED, WITH REFERENCE TO PUBLISHING OPPORTUNITIES,IMPLICATIONS FOR PRINT INDUSTRY MARKETS AND PRODUCTION METHODS